node.text:
Like most other people, @tylerbossetti didn't have a perfect upbringing but he didn't let that get in his way.

He got out of his toxic environment by becoming a door-to-door salesman and eventually transitioning into the mortgage industry, where he would learn the ins and outs of real estate.

He then used that knowledge to build a real estate fund that helps others invest in great real estate deals without doing any of the work.

If he can do it, anyone can.

Go follow him, he's putting out some great content @tylerbossetti 🔥

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on September 01, 2021 tagging @tylerbossetti. May be an image of text that says 'Tyler Bossetti @tylerbossetti 1- Your environment can kill your dreams. If you're consistently hanging around people who don't have the same goals or ambitions as you, they will end up bringing you down. Find a good circle that you can build with.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on September 01, 2021 tagging @tylerbossetti. May be an image of text that says 'Tyler Bossetti @tylerbossetti 2- Your past doesn't determine your future. If you grow up in a toxic household or a small town, you can't et that determine your future. Letting go of my past helped me reach my goals much quicker.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on September 01, 2021 tagging @tylerbossetti. May be an image of text that says 'Tyler Bossetti @tylerbossetti Money isn't evil. If you're around the wrong people, you'll perceive money as evil if you make too much of it. Focusing on all of the people could help and the things I could do with money changed my perspective.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on September 01, 2021 tagging @tylerbossetti. May be an image of text that says 'Tyler Bossetti @tylerbossetti After years of battling with bad influences and a toxic environment as a kid, I decided to build a real estate fund. Nothing fancy, but I do help ordinary people nvest in real estate without doing the work. If you want more content like this, follow me.'.
